🛡️ Red Team OS — Installation Guide (VMware Image)
A custom-built Red Team Operating System pre-loaded with offensive security tools and configurations, optimized for adversary simulations and real-world cyber exercises.

📥 Step 1: Download the Prebuilt VM
Download the exported virtual machine image from the following Google Drive link:

🔗 Download Red Team OS : https://drive.google.com/file/d/1G_n_nOdZL0Fe77g9_GD6iSe1jEvbKMEg/view?usp=sharing

📦 Step 2: Extract the Files
Once the .zip or .7z archive is downloaded:

Extract it using a utility like WinRAR, 7-Zip, or macOS Archive Utility.

You should see the following files after extraction:

kali-linux-2025.1a-vmware-amd64.ovf

kali-linux-2025.1a-vmware-amd64-disk1.vmdk

💻 Step 3: Import into VMware
Open VMware Workstation or VMware Fusion.

Go to File → Open.

Select the .ovf file (kali-linux-2025.1a-vmware-amd64.ovf).

Click Continue and follow the on-screen instructions to import the VM.

Once imported, start the VM.

🛠️ Default Credentials (If Applicable)
Username: root or kali

Password: toor or kali

(You may change this based on your hardened image settings.)

🧰 Included Tools
Cloud Enumeration

Exploitation Frameworks

Privilege Escalation Scripts

Recon Tools

Wireless & RF Testing Utilities

(Refer to tools.md for the full list if bundled.)

🧯 Tips
Make sure virtualization is enabled in BIOS/EFI.

Allocate at least 4 CPU cores, 8GB RAM, and 30GB+ disk space for smooth performance.

Take a snapshot after the first boot for rollback.

